If $$\left[ {\matrix{
   x &amp; { - 3i} &amp; 1  \cr 
   y &amp; 1 &amp; i  \cr 
   0 &amp; {2i} &amp; { - i}  \cr 

 } } \right] = 6 + 11i$$, then what are the values of x and y respectively?

en.explanation:
We have, $$\left| {\matrix{
   x &amp; { - 3i} &amp; 1  \cr 
   y &amp; 1 &amp; i  \cr 
   0 &amp; {2i} &amp; { - i}  \cr 

 } } \right| = 6 + 11i$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x( - i + 2) - y( - 3 - 2i) = 6 + 11i$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 2x + 3y + ( - x + 2y)i = 6 + 11i$$<br><br>On equating real and imaginary parts, on both sides,<br><br>we get $$2x + 3y = 6$$ ..... (i)<br><br>and $$ - x + 2y = 11$$ ..... (ii)<br><br>On solving Eqs. (i) and (ii), we get<br><br>$$x =  - 3$$<br><br>and $$y = 4$$

