If $$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$, then the matrix A is a/an

en.explanation:
We have, $$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\left| A \right| =  - 1$$<br><br>Since, $$\left| A \right| \ne 0$$<br><br>Hence, A is not singular.<br><br>$${A^2} = A.A = \left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right].\left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>A<sup>2</sup> = I<br><br>Hence, A is involutory matrix.

