If $$A = \left( {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right)$$ and $${A^2} - kA - {I_2} = O$$, where I<sub>2</sub> is the 2 $$\times$$ 2 identity matrix, then what is the value of k?

en.explanation:
We have,<br><br>$$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $${A^2} = A.A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right]\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {1.1 + 2.2} &amp; {1.2 + 2.3}  \cr 
   {2.1 + 3.2} &amp; {2.2 + 3.3}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   5 &amp; 8  \cr 
   8 &amp; {13}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>Now, it is given that,<br><br>$${A^2} - kA - {I_2} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \left[ {\matrix{
   5 &amp; 8  \cr 
   8 &amp; {13}  \cr 

 } } \right] - \left[ {\matrix{
   k &amp; {2k}  \cr 
   {2k} &amp; {3k}  \cr 

 } } \right] - \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right] = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; 8  \cr 
   8 &amp; {12}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   k &amp; {2k}  \cr 
   {2k} &amp; {3k}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow k = 4$$

