What should be the value of x, so that the matrix $$\left( {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 4  \cr 
   { - 8} &amp; x  \cr 

 } } \right)$$ does not have an inverse?

en.explanation:
Let $$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 4  \cr 
   { - 8} &amp; x  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>Matrix does not have an inverse, if<br><br>$$\left| A \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 2x + 32 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 2x =  - 32$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x =  - {{32} \over 2}$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x =  - 16$$

